# Nightly at 02:00 UTC (docs/10-operations.md section 1). Output goes to the
# container's stdout/stderr (PID 1's fds) so `docker compose logs backup`
# shows dump/upload/prune progress and failures.
0 2 * * * /backup.sh >>/proc/1/fd/1 2>>/proc/1/fd/2

# Exam-day belt: poll every 5 minutes for a same-day trigger row written by
# quiz.Service.Publish. A no-op query when nothing is pending, so this is
# cheap enough to run tightly; runs the same dump/upload/prune as above when
# a quiz was published to start today.
*/5 * * * * /check-trigger.sh >>/proc/1/fd/1 2>>/proc/1/fd/2
